{{notability|Biographies|date=April 2016}} '''Ion Hobana''' (January 25, 1931, [[Sânnicolau Mare]]&nbsp;– February 22, 2011, [[Bucharest]]) was a [[Romania]]n science fiction writer, literary critic and [[ufologist]].<ref name="WashingtonPost2011">[https://www.washingtonpost.com/wp-dyn/content/article/2011/02/23/AR2011022302460.html Romanian SF writer Ion Hobana dies at 80] ''The Washington Post'' (February 23, 2011). Retrieved on February 25, 2011.</ref> Ion Hobana is a literary pseudonym, the writer's real name being Aurelian Manta Roşie.
==Bibliography==
