'''Mangala Devi Singh''' ({{lang-ne|मंगलादेवी सिंह}}) was a pioneer feminist and prominent democratic right activist of Nepal. She spent many years in jail for movements related to the same. She was the founder of [[Nepal Woman Association]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://nnv.nepalnews.com/videoplay1.php?id=1290|title=Mangala Devi Remembered|date=August 26, 2008|publisher=Nepalnews Videos : Mercantile Communications Pvt. Ltd.|accessdate=12 March 2011}}</ref> She was the wife of a leading [[Nepali Congress]] Leader [[Ganesh Man Singh]].

