{{Infobox rugby biography | name = Patats Cloete | image = Patats Cloete.jpg | caption = | birth_name = Henry Arthur Cloete | nickname = | birth_date = {{birth date|1873|6|15|df=y}} | birth_place = [[Cape Town]], [[South Africa]] | death_date = {{Death date and age|1959|3|29|1873|6|15|df=yes}} | death_place = [[Bulawayo]], [[Rhodesia and Nyasaland]] | height = | weight = | ru_position = [[Rugby union positions#Forwards|Forward]] | ru_amateurclubs = | ru_amupdate = | ru_nationalteam = [[South Africa national rugby union team|South Africa]] | ru_nationalyears = 1896 | ru_nationalcaps = 1 | ru_nationalpoints = (0) | ru_ntupdate = 19 July 2010 | ru_province = [[Western Province (rugby team)|Western Province]] | ru_provinceyears = | ru_provincecaps = | ru_provincepoints = | ru_provinceupdate = 19 July 2010 | relatives = | school = | university = }} '''Henry Arthur "Patats" Cloete''' (15 June 1873 – 29 March 1959) was a [[South Africa]]n international [[rugby union]] player. Born in [[Cape Town]], he first played provincial rugby for [[Western Province (rugby team)|Western Province]]. He made his only [[Test match (rugby union)|Test]] appearance for [[South Africa national rugby union team|South Africa]] during [[1896 British Lions tour to South Africa|Great Britain's 1896 tour]]. He played as a [[Rugby union positions#Forwards|forward]] for the 4th Test of the series, a 5–0 win at [[Newlands Stadium]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.genslin.us/bokke/ |title=Patats Cloete |publisher=Springbok Rugby Hall of Fame|accessdate=2010-09-05}}</ref> Cloete died in 1959, in [[Bulawayo]], at the age of 85.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.scrum.com/southafrica/rugby/player/1238.html |title=South Africa / Players & Officials / Patats Cloete |publisher=Scrum |accessdate=2010-09-05}}</ref>
